<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-61-0586 </DOCNO><TEXT>Invasive cardiovascular diagnostic procedures involve a finite risk andtherefore can be recommended only when the benefit appears to exceedthe risk by a substantial margin. The risk/benefit ratio varies not onlywith the procedure concerned but with the status of the vascular system,concomitant diseases, and the risks of both the suspected illness andits treatment. The risks inherent in the procedures per se are detailedin the sections to follow.</TEXT></DOC>